# Project Internationalization Standards

This is an **international open-source project**. All code, docs, and agent output follow these rules.

## Language Policy

| Layer | Language | Notes |
|-------|----------|-------|
| Source code | **English** | Classes, functions, variables, enums, comments |
| Git commits & PRs | **English** | Conventional Commits format |
| Architecture docs | **English** | `docs/` folder |
| User-facing strings | **i18n keys** | Never hardcode UI text in code |
| Domain glossary | **English** | Business terms in English; localized labels via i18n |

## i18n Rules

- Use Android string resources (`strings.xml`) with locale variants (`values-pt-rBR/`, `values-es/`, etc.).
- Key naming: `feature_component_description` (snake_case), e.g. `price_search_city_hint`.
- Default locale: `en` (values/strings.xml).
- Brazilian Portuguese is the first additional locale (`pt-BR`) given the ANP data source.
- Format dates, numbers, and currency with `Locale`-aware APIs — never manual string concatenation.
- ANP source data arrives in Portuguese; normalize to domain enums in English at the Infrastructure boundary.

## Code Examples

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD — hardcoded UI text
Text("Preço médio da gasolina")

// ✅ GOOD — i18n key
Text(stringResource(R.string.fuel_average_price_label))

// ❌ BAD — Portuguese identifier
fun buscarPrecosPorCidade(cidade: String)

// ✅ GOOD — English identifier, localized output
fun searchPricesByCity(city: City): List<FuelPrice>
```

## Agent Behavior

- Write all new code, docs, and commit messages in English.
- When discussing with the user in Portuguese, still produce English code and docs unless explicitly asked otherwise.
- Add i18n keys for every user-visible string in the same PR that introduces the UI.
